## Session goal

Land Phase 1 of the AMI v2 rebuild: validate the
"download from biobakery + UserData page-cache warmup" pattern on the
single MetaPhlAn DB used by profile_taxa (vJan25). Once proven, Phase 2
extends the same pattern to vOct22 / profile_function.

Diagnosed during the prior I16 max005 resume run:

  - profile_taxa (SRR36835853) hit the 1h Batch attempt timeout.
  - ~12 min of that hour were burned by MetaPhlAn 4.2.4 doing on-the-fly
    DB prep (decompress .bz2, build joined fasta, bowtie2-build).
  - Live measurements on PID 5262 showed ~33 min in state D
    (uninterruptible disk wait) doing cold-cache mmap of vOct22 from
    EBS at ~5.6 MB/s — IOPS-throttled at the gp3 baseline.

Two issues filed:
  - I20 — pre-warm MetaPhlAn page cache in worker UserData
  - I21 — bake MetaPhlAn DB prep into the Packer AMI from biobakery

================================================================================
1. PLAYBOOK + ISSUE NARROWING
================================================================================

Playbook (infra/playbook-ami-v2-rebuild.md) and issues I20/I21 narrowed
to **Phase 1 = profile_taxa / vJan25 only**. Phase 2 deferred (vOct22
/ profile_function — same mechanism, separate validation).

Phase 1 keeps the existing S3 sync intact (vOct22 still served from
cjb-gutz-s3-demo as today). The new Packer step replaces only the
vJan25 directory contents with the prepared form fetched directly
from biobakery via `metaphlan --install`.

Decision: source vJan25 from the official biobakery distribution rather
than copying through cjb-gutz-s3-demo. Two upsides:
  - Removes ~54 GB of redundant data from our bucket (when Phase 2
    also moves vOct22 to biobakery).
  - Canonical version pinning — biobakery's distribution for a given
    index name is immutable.

