3. AMI BUILD #1 — FAILED AFTER 11:34 (FLAG TYPO)
================================================================================

Pre-flight clean: queue empty, no orphan screen sessions, prior AMI
(ami-0b87926a60df7043e) still in SSM as rollback target.

Build log: logs/ami-build-20260428-154810.log
Packer instance: i-002d4823d1b1a5b5f (terminated by Packer cleanup).

Failure point: `metaphlan --install` invocation rejected one of the
flags from the original biobakery forum example:

    metaphlan: error: unrecognized arguments: --bowtie2db

MetaPhlAn 4.2.4's flag is `--db_dir`, not `--bowtie2db` (the forum post
referenced was for an older release). Help output from the failed run
confirmed the 4.2.4 form: `--install --index <name> --db_dir <path>`.

No rollback needed — Packer doesn't update SSM until success, so the
old AMI ID stayed published.

