6. AMI BUILD #2 — COMPLETED, WITH PACKER WAIT-TIMEOUT EDGE CASE
================================================================================

Build log: logs/ami-build-20260428-161829.log
Packer instance: i-0d559b92c1fa2626f (terminated by Packer cleanup).

Build content milestones, all clean:
  16:18  Packer instance launched
  16:29  metaphlan --install begins
  17:12  Decompressing .bz2 fastas
  17:22  Joining FASTAs
  17:23  Removing intermediates; "Download complete"
  17:23  Validation block: 6 .bt2l files in vJan25/ (>= 4 required)
  17:23  Packer "Stopping the source instance"
  17:24  AMI ami-0b82e0161299a01ea created (state pending)

But: Packer's aws_polling.max_attempts=120 (60 min wait cap) was too
tight for the 500 GB snapshot. Packer's wait-for-ready expired before
the snapshot reached 'available', so packer build exited non-zero
even though the AMI was real. build-ami.sh has `set -euo pipefail`,
so the SSM put-parameter step never ran.

Two follow-up commits pre-empted this for next time:
  - 4ccfeca "Make Packer build resilient to slow AMI snapshots"
    - worker-ami.pkr.hcl: max_attempts 120 -> 240 (2 h cap)
    - build-ami.sh: drop `set -e`, fall back to EC2 describe-images
      query if packer-manifest.json missing, then `aws ec2 wait
      image-available` before publishing to SSM.
  - c8752b9 "Update operational docs: SNS, log group, SSM resolution"

Manual recovery for THIS build: polled until AMI flipped to
'available' (~17:55 UTC, snapshot was at 71% when checked, finished
~01:08 UTC the next day after we'd done other work). Published
manually:
  aws ssm put-parameter --name /nf-reads-profiler/ami-id \
    --type String --value ami-0b82e0161299a01ea \
    --overwrite --region us-east-2

